OL,4,CJohn Lydon calls Sex Pistols ruling
OL,5,Cdumbfounding and destructive
OL,6, John Lydon has railed against a High
OL,7, Court ruling allowing Sex Pistols music
OL,8, to be used in a new TV drama, calling
OL,9, it "dumbfounding and destructive".
OL,11,FIn his first public statement on the
OL,12,Fdecision, the singer said he feared the
OL,13,Fdrama would be "extremely negative".
OL,15,FFormer drummer Paul Cook and guitarist
OL,16,FSteve Jones had sued Lydon, aka Johnny
OL,17,FRotten, after he tried to veto the use
OL,18,Fof the punk group's songs.
OL,20,FA judge ruled they could overrule him
OL,21,Fdue to a "majority rule" agreement.
